cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with unsupervised learning and segmentation of hyperspectral images, which is a problem in computer vision. The proposed technique involves combining geometric estimation of class modes with a diffusion-inspired labeling that incorporates both spectral and spatial information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of unsupervised learning and active learning techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of diffusion distance and nonlinear diffusion processes suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
